  "text": "As a notational point, I write the Kronecker delta as δ (., .) , and the Dirac delta as δ (.) . I assume the reader knows basic terminology concerning Bayesian networks, e.g., directed acyclic graphs (DAGs), their roots, leaves, children, parents, etc., [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . I indicate entropy of a distribution p(X) as S(p(X)), or just S(p) for short [CITATION_3] . I write the mutual information of a distribution p(X, Y ) as I p (X; Y ), or just I(X; Y ) for short. More generally, I write the multi-information of a joint distribution over a set of random variables, p(X 1 , X 2 , ...) by",
